 aims-os-core,
# Locale and timezone packages are pulled by aims-os-core. This package
# is intentionally empty at v2.1 — it exists as the slot for centre-
# specific content that we'll layer on as we go:
#   * Firefox bookmarks pointing at the AIMS Mbour intranet, library,
#     mail and learning platforms (deployed via /etc/skel and
#     /usr/lib/firefox-esr/distribution).
#   * Senegal-themed wallpaper variants (campus shots, Mbour beach,
#     local cultural patterns).
#   * Calamares post-install hooks that drop the Senegal-specific
#     CUPS printer PPDs, AIMS WiFi profile snippet, etc.
#   * Course content snapshots for AIMS Senegal's 2026-2027 curriculum
#     (mirrored under /usr/share/aims-os/courses/senegal/).
#
# Sibling centre packages (aims-os-centre-southafrica, -cameroon,
# -ghana, -rwanda, -tanzania) can be added later without touching the
# universal slim layer. See docs/maintenance/policy/ for the multi-
# centre roadmap.
Description: AIMS OS — AIMS Senegal (Mbour) centre profile
 Centre profile for AIMS Senegal (Mbour campus). Layers the Senegal-
 specific bookmarks, wallpapers, intranet wiring, printer profiles
 and course content snapshots on top of the universal aims-os-core
 baseline.
 .
 This package is the dedicated slot for centre customisation. The
 universal layers (aims-os-core, aims-os-desktop, aims-os-math) stay
 free of Senegal-specific hard-coding so a future
 aims-os-centre-{southafrica,cameroon,ghana,rwanda,tanzania} can be
 added without refactoring the base.
 .
 v2.1 ships this metapackage empty (Depends: aims-os-core only) — it
 marks the architecture without committing to specific Senegal content
 yet. Content will be added incrementally as the AIMS Mbour deployment
 grows.
